 - [[vocals]]\n* [[Michael Boddicker]] - [[synthesizer]]\n* Joe Chemay - background vocals\n* [[Bob Glaub]] - [[bass guitar]]\n* [[Jim Haas]] - background vocals\n* Jon Joyce - background vocals\n* [[Michael Landau]] - [[guitar]]\n* Greg Mathieson - synthesizer, [[keyboard instrument|keyboards]]\n{{col-2}}\n* Lisa Sarna - background vocals\n* [[Stephanie Spruill]] - background vocals\n* Julia Tillman Waters - background vocals\n* Carlos Vega - drums\n* [[Trevor Veitch]] - guitar\n* Maxine Willard Waters - background vocals\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Chart history===\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-break}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1982\u201383)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n|Australia (Kent Music Report)\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|32|artist=Laura Branigan|song=Gloria}}\n|-\n|Canada ''[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]'' Top Singles \n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland2|4|artist=Laura Branigan}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|6|artist=Laura Branigan|song=Gloria}}\n|-\n|South Africa (Singles Chart)\n|align=\"center\"|9\n|-\n{{singlechart|UKsinglesbyname|6|artist=Laura Branigan|song=Gloria}}\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref>''Joel Whitburn's Top Pop Singles 1955-2002'', 2005, Record Research Inc., {{ISBN|978-0898201550}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|US [[Cash Box (magazine)|''Cash Box'']] Top 100<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tropicalglen.com/Archives/80s_files/19821127.html |title=Cash Box Top 100 Singles, November 27, 1982 |access-date=August 30, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160531112310/http://tropicalglen.com/Archives/80s_files/19821127.html |archive-date=May 31, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Chart (2019)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n|US [[Digital Songs]] ([[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']])<ref name=\"billboard.com\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|46\n|}\n{{Col-break}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1982)\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Rank\n|-\n|Canada<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?brws_s=1&file_num=nlc008388.6167&type=1&interval=24&PHPSESSID=mhe12pta2k83e08udtq66ot062|title=Item Display - RPM - Library and Archives Canada|work=collectionscanada.gc.ca|access-date=2017-08-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160811145442/http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?brws_s=1&file_num=nlc008388.6167&type=1&interval=24&PHPSESSID=mhe12pta2k83e08udtq66ot062|archive-date=2016-08-11|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|14\n|-\n|US ''Cash Box''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tropicalglen.com/Archives/80s_files/1982YESP.html |title=Cash Box Year-End Charts: Top 100 Pop Singles, December 25, 1982 |access-date=August 30, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711062300/http://tropicalglen.com/Archives/80s_files/1982YESP.html |archive-date=July 11, 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|26\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>[http://www.musicoutfitters.com/topsongs/1982.htm Musicoutfitters.com]</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|75\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1983)\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Rank\n|-\n|Australia<ref name=\"Australian Chart Book 1970\u20131992\">{{cite book|title=Australian Chart Book 1970\u20131992|format=doc|last=Kent|first=David|authorlink=David Kent (historian)|publisher=Australian Chart Book, St Ives, N.S.W |year=1993|isbn=0-646-11917-6|title-link=Kent Music Report}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n|-\n|New Zealand<ref>{{cite web|title= End of Year Charts 1983 |publisher= [[Recorded Music NZ]] |accessdate= July 16, 2017 |url= http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/?chart=3872}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|49\n|-\n|UK<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.uk-charts.top-source.info/top-100-1983.shtml |title = Top 100 1983 - UK Music Charts}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|73\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>[http://www.musicoutfitters.com/topsongs/1983.htm Musicoutfitters.com]</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|56\n|-\n|}\n\n===All-time charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! Chart (1958-2018)\n! Position\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100-60th-anniversary|title=Billboard Hot 100 60th Anniversary Interactive Chart|work=Billboard|accessdate=10 December 2018}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|386\n|}\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Certifications===\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Canada|type=single|title=Gloria|artist=Laura Branigan|award=Platinum|certyear=1983|relyear=1982|salesamount=100,000}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|type=single|title=Gloria|artist=Laura Branigan|award=Gold|certyear=1983|relyear=1982}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|type=single|title=Gloria|artist=Laura Branigan|award=Platinum|certyear=1995|relyear=1982}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==Other versions and inclusions==\n\n===Early years===\nA [[Czech Republic|Czech]] rendering of \"Gloria\", titled \"D\u00edvka Gloria\", was a local success for [[:cs:V\u00edt\u011bzslav V\u00e1vra|V\u00edt\u011bzslav V\u00e1vra]] in 1980;<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tn.nova.cz/zpravy/zajimavosti/zpivajici-bubenik-vita-vavra-zkousi-to-porad-dal.html |title=Zp\u00edvaj\u00edc\u00ed buben\u00edk V\u00ed\u0165a V\u00e1vra: Jsem m\u00e1ma v dom\u00e1cnosti |publisher=TN.cz |date=January 4, 2012}}</ref> as well as for the [[Estonia]]n rendering of \"Gloria\" recorded by [[:et:Mait Maltis|Mait Maltis]] in the same year. In 1982, [[Sylvie Vartan]] recorded \"Gloria\" with Branigan's song lyrics, while [[Lena Valaitis]] had a single release of \"Gloria\" with new [[German language|German]] lyrics written by [[Michael Kunze]], and production by [[Jack White (music producer)|Jack White]]. In 1983, [[Carola H\u00e4ggkvist]] recorded a [[Swedish language|Swedish]] rendering of \"Gloria\" \u2013 lyrics by [[Ingela Forsman]] \u2013 for her album ''[[Fr\u00e4mling]]'';<ref>{{cite web|url=http://smdb.kb.se/catalog/id/001886146|title=Fr\u00e4mling|publisher=Svensk mediedatabas|language=Swedish|date=1983|accessdate=3 October 2015}}</ref> while [[:fi:Mona Carita|Mona Carita]] recorded a [[Finnish language|Finnish]] rendering of the song for her album ''Mik\u00e4 Fiilis!''\n\n\"Gloria\" has been used internationally in [[TV commercial]]s for products as diverse as [[beer]] and [[flour]]; while another version of the song, amended into an advertising jingle with lyrics to suit the product, and soundalike vocalist to Branigan, was used in an [[Australia]]n TV commercial for the 1984 [[Mitsubishi Cordia]].<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CKFTPCgRs5g</ref>\n\nPrior to Branigan's version repeating its U.S. success in the [[United Kingdom|U.K.]], British singer [[Elkie Brooks]] recorded her version of \"Gloria\", which was unreleased prior to inclusion in the 1986 album ''[[The Very Best of Elkie Brooks (1986 album)|The Very Best of Elkie Brooks]]''. Australian singer [[Julie Anthony (singer)|Julie Anthony]] also recorded \"Gloria\" for her 1983 [[cover version|covers album]] ''What a Feeling''.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.discogs.com/Julie-Anthony-What-A-Feeling/release/5693957 |title = Julie Anthony - What a Feeling}}</ref>\n\n===Later years===\nBroadcast in November 23, 2000, [[Debbie Reynolds]] sings a snippet of \"Gloria\" in the \"Lows in the Mid-Eighties\" episode of the [[NBC]] sitcom ''[[Will & Grace]]'', where she performs the song as the character \"Bobbi Adler\" in a sequence set in 1985. Australian [[Young Divas]] included \"Gloria\" on their [[Young Divas (album)|self-titled album]] in 2006. In 2010, [[South Korea]]n actress [[Bae Doona]] headlined a television series named \"Gloria\", where Bae portrays an aspiring singer who gets her start and ascends to fame by singing a [[Korean language|Korean]] cover of song \"Gloria\".{{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n\n[[David Civera]] recorded a [[Spanish language|Spanish]] rendering of \"Gloria\" for his album ''A ritmo de clasicos'' in 2011, the same year that [[Sergio Dalma]] recorded another Spanish version of \"Gloria\" on his album ''[[Via Dalma II]]''; the album lasted five weeks at number 1 in [[Spain]], and earned quadruple-platinum status. Airing in December 2011, Sergio Dalma also performed the song on an [[RTVE]] special called ''Via Dalma'', where Tozzi was also among the guests.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rtve.es/alacarta/videos/especiales-navidad/sergio-dalma-via-dalma/1280393/ |title=Sergio Dalma - Via Dalma, Especiales de Navidad |publisher=[[RTVE]] |date=December 24, 2011}}</ref>\n\n[[:nl:Jo Vally|Jo Vally]] recorded a [[Flemish language|Flemish]] rendering of \"Gloria\" for his 2012 album ''Zingt zuiderse klassiekers''; the track reached number 15 on the [[Ultratop]] chart. [[Gloria Trevi]] performed \"Gloria\" as an opening number in concert, and recorded a studio version of Spanish lyrics completely different from the original, released in February 2012.{{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n\nOn June 12, 2019, while in St. Louis, [[Phish]] covered the song following the [[St. Louis Blues]]'s win over the [[Boston Bruins]] in the [[2019 Stanley Cup Finals]].<ref>https://twitter.com/Phish_FTR/status/1139006702274134017</ref> The Blues would play the song after every win in 2019.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Music}}\n* [[Music of Italy]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{MetroLyrics song|umberto-tozzi|gloria|version=[[Laura Branigan]]'s cover}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Laura Branigan singles}}\n{{St. Louis Blues}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gloria (Umberto Tozzi Song)}}\n[[Category:1979 songs]]\n[[Category:1979 singles]]\n[[Category:Pop ballads]]\n[[Category:Umberto Tozzi songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Umberto Tozzi]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Giancarlo Bigazzi]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:1982 singles]]\n[[Category:Laura Branigan songs]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Australia]]\n[[Category:RPM Top Singles number-one singles]]\n[[Category:2004 singles]]\n[[Category:Hi-NRG songs]]\n[[Category:2011 singles]]\n[[Category:House music songs]]\n[[Category:CBS Records singles]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records singles]]\n[[Category:St. Louis Blues]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name = Gloria\n| cover = Umberto-tozzi-gloria.jpg\n| alt =\n| caption = Artwork for some releases, including Italian release\n| type = single\n| artist = [[Umberto Tozzi]]\n| album = [[Gloria (Umberto Tozzi album)|Gloria]]\n| B-side = Aria di lei\n| released = {{Start date|df=y|1979|6}}\n| format = {{flatlist|\n*[[7-inch single|7\"]]\n*[[12-inch single|12\"]]\n*[[CD single|CD]]\n}}\n| recorded = By Zeke Lund\n| studio = Union Studios Munich\n\n| venue =\n| genre = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[Dance music|dance]]\n* [[disco]]\n}}\n| length = {{Duration|m=4|s=25}}\n| label = {{flatlist|\n* [[Compagnia Generale del Disco|CGD]]\n* [[CBS Records International|CBS]]\n}}\n| writer = {{flatlist|\n*Umberto Tozzi\n*[[Giancarlo Bigazzi]]\n*[[Jonathan King]] {{small|(English translation)}}\n}}\n| producer = Umberto Tozzi\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year =\n| next_title =\n| next_year =\n| misc = {{External music video|header= Audio|{{YouTube|8Zs7VWqNGHg|\"Gloria\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Gloria'''\" ({{IPA-it|\u02c8\u0261l\u0254\u02d0rja}}) is a 1979 [[love song]] that became an international [[hit song|hit]]. The song was originally written and composed in [[Italian language|Italian]] by [[Umberto Tozzi]] and [[Giancarlo Bigazzi]], and afterwards translated to [[English language|English]] by [[Jonathan King]]. A 1982 [[cover version]] by American singer [[Laura Branigan]] sold over one million singles in the United States alone.\n\n==Umberto Tozzi version==\n\n===Background===\n[[Umberto Tozzi]] first recorded \"Gloria\" in 1979;<ref name=\"utozzigloria\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KTM_qG_NPC8 |title=Video of Umberto Tozzi singing his original 'Gloria' in Italian |publisher=[[YouTube]] |accessdate=April 1, 2010}}</ref> that summer the song stayed on the [[Italy|Italian]] Top-10 chart for sixteen weeks, six of them at number 2. The song stayed four weeks at number 1 in both, [[Switzerland]] and \u2013 in a translated version \u2013 [[Spain]]. That same year saw Tozzi's \"Gloria\" achieve hit status in [[Austria]] at number 4, [[Belgium]] at number 3, the [[Netherlands]] at number 21, [[France]] at number 3, and [[Germany]] where the track reached number 8.<ref name=\"topcharts\">{{Cite web |url=http://tsort.info/music/8w9fef.htm/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110914100100/http://tsort.info/music/8w9fef.htm |title=Song artist 746 - Umberto Tozzi |publisher=The World's Music Charts |archivedate=September 14, 2011}}</ref>\n\nTozzi's \"Gloria\" is a [[love song]],<ref name=\"utozzigloria\"/><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://lyricstranslate.com/en/Gloria-Gloria.html |title=Translation of \"Gloria\" by Umberto Tozzi from Italian to English |publisher=Lyrics Translate}}</ref> as is the first [[English language|English]] rendering of the song,<ref name=\"utozzijkinggloria\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cfh96y4G9nM |title=Video of Umberto Tozzi singing the original 'Gloria' in English |publisher=[[YouTube]] |accessdate=July 8, 2011}}</ref> recorded by its original English-language lyricist, [[Jonathan King]], in November 1979;<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/search/singles/Jimmy |title=The Official Charts Company - Jonathan King - Gloria |publisher=[[Official Charts Company]] }}</ref> Tozzi later recorded and performed King's translated version of \"Gloria\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.45cat.com/record/sepc7415 |title=Umberto Tozzi - Gloria (English Version) / Aria Di Lei |publisher=45cat |accessdate=June 25, 2013}}</ref> He also re-recorded the song with [[Trevor Veitch]]'s and [[Laura Branigan]]'s English lyrics; this version appears on his 2002 release, ''The Best of Umberto Tozzi''.\n\nIn 2011, the song was brought up to date with a set of new [[house music|house]] mixes by [[Alex Gaudino]] and Jason Rooney.<ref name=\"Gloria 2011\"/> The music video stars Umberto and Natasha Tozzi.<ref name=\"housegloria\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BJAaQpBUQZ8 |title=Official music video of 'Gloria 2011' |publisher=[[YouTube]] |accessdate=February 20, 2012}}</ref>\n\nTozzi's original version of \"Gloria\" was a soundtrack selection for two distinct films in 2013, ''[[The Wolf of Wall Street (2013 film)|The Wolf of Wall Street]]''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://theschleicherspin.com/2013/12/26/martin-scorseses-jackass-or-the-wolf-of-wall-street/ |title=Martin Scorcese's Jackass or The Wolf of Wall Street |publisher=The Schleicher Spin |date=December 26, 2013}}</ref> and ''[[Gloria (2013 film)|Gloria]].''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.charlestoncitypaper.com/charleston/quiet-and-unpretentious-gloria-realistically-captivates/Content?oid=4871768 |title=Quiet & Unpretentious Gloria Realistically Captivates |publisher=Charleston City Paper |date=February 26, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Lyrical content===\nIn his song of [[Jonathan King]]'s translated lyrics, Tozzi, who takes the role of the song's main character, tells that he is dreaming about an imaginary woman named Gloria. He describes his living days as misery, but when he dreams of Gloria, he says his nights are liberty. The protagonist describes Gloria as his queen imagination that comes from his fascination, not from any kind of fantasy. He further elaborates that he has always set Gloria free from him, just as he has set freedom from reality. He then tells that his friends think he is crazy, but he argues his point that they have never met Gloria (so far, he has no proof of her actual existence); but one day when he finds her, he says his friends will talk about Gloria's beauty and her loyalty. To accomplish the goal of realizing his dreams despite everyone else's protests, the protagonist sets all his life to search for Gloria until he meets her in reality, and then promises to hold her, to touch her, and to keep her because he loves Gloria.<ref name=\"utozzijkinggloria\"/>\n\n===Track listings===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = 7\" single<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.discogs.com/Umberto-Tozzi-Gloria/release/727818 |title=Umberto Tozzi - Gloria (Vinyl, 7\") at Discogs |publisher=[[Discogs]] |accessdate=October 7, 2015}}</ref>\n| title1          = Gloria\n| length1         = 4:25\n| title2          = Aria di lei\n| length2         = 4:10\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = 12\" single<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.discogs.com/Umberto-Tozzi-Gloria/release/2985347 |title=Umberto Tozzi - Gloria (Vinyl, 12\") at Discogs |publisher=[[Discogs]] |accessdate=October 7, 2015}}</ref>\n| title1          = Gloria\n| note1           = 12\" disco mix\n| length1         = 7:05\n| title2          = [[Mama (Umberto Tozzi and Laura Branigan song)|Mama]]\n| length2         = 5:07\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = 12\" single {{nobold|(UK)}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.discogs.com/Umberto-Tozzi-Gloria/release/1232262 |title=Umberto Tozzi - Gloria (Vinyl, 12\" UK) at Discogs |publisher=[[Discogs]] |accessdate=October 7, 2015}}</ref>\n| title1          = Gloria\n| note1           = English version\n| length1         = 6:30\n| title2          = Gloria\n| note2           = Italian version\n| length2         = 4:25\n| title3          = Aria di lei\n| length3         = 4:10\n}}\n\n{{col-break}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = CD single {{nobold|\u2013 2001 version}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.discogs.com/Umberto-Tozzi-Gloria/release/4374370 |title=Umberto Tozzi - Gloria (CD) at Discogs |publisher=[[Discogs]] |accessdate=October 7, 2015}}</ref>\n| title1          = Gloria\n| note1           = 2001 version\n| length1         = 4:57\n| title2          = Gloria\n| note2           = Remixland radio edit\n| length2         = 4:25\n| title3          = Gloria\n| note3           = Remixland extended\n| length3         = 5:39\n| title4          = Gloria\n| note4           = La Fabrique Du Sons dub remix\n| length4         = 6:03\n| title5          = Gloria\n| note5           = Original version\n| length5         = 4:55\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = Digital download {{nobold|\u2013 2011 remixes}}<ref name=\"Gloria 2011\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00CJE9OCA/ |title=Gloria 2011: Umberto Tozzi |date=July 5, 2011}}</ref>\n| title1          = Gloria 2011\n| note1           = Club edit\n| length1         = 4:09\n| title2          = Gloria 2011\n| note2           = Sorrentino & Zara Italian radio mix\n| length2         = 4:25\n| title3          = Gloria 2011\n| note3           = Sorrentino & Zara English radio mix\n| length3         = 4:25\n| title4          = Gloria 2011\n| note4           = Club mix\n| length4         = 7:13\n| title5          = Gloria 2011\n| note5           = Sorrentino & Zara Italian extended mix\n| length5         = 6:12\n| title6          = Gloria 2011\n| note6           = Sorrentino & Zara English extended mix\n| length6         = 6:27\n}}\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Personnel===\n*[[Umberto Tozzi]] - vocals, chorus\n*[[Greg Mathieson]] - conductor, piano, keyboards\n*[[Barry Morgan (musician)|Barry Morgan]] - drums\n*[[Mats Bj\u00f6rklund]] - guitar\n*[[Les Hurdle]] - bass\n*[[Filarmonica Di Monaco]] - strings\n*[[Euro Cristiani]] - chorus\n\n===Charts===\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-break}}\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1979)\n!Peak #\n|-\n|Australia ([[Kent Music Report]])<ref>{{cite book| title=Australian Chart Chronicles (1940\u20132008)|last=Kent|first=David|publisher=Australian Chart Book, 2009| location= Turramurra NSW|year=2009|isbn= 978-0-646-51203-7}}</ref>\n|\n{| class=\"